%I A395241 #29 Jun 15 2026 17:24:44
%S A395241 0,7,44,135,304,575,972,1519,2240,3159,4300,5687,7344,9295,11564,
%T A395241 14175,17152,20519,24300,28519,33200,38367,44044,50255,57024,64375,
%U A395241 72332,80919,90160,100079,110700,122047,134144,147015,160684,175175,190512,206719,223820,241839,260800
%N A395241 a(n) = n^2*(4*n + 3).
%C A395241 a(n) is the number of cells with at least two even coordinates in a cubical grid of side 2n+1, with coordinates numbered from 1; equivalently a(n) = (2n+1)^3 - A103532(n).
%C A395241 For n = 1 these are the 7 cells removed in the first step of the Menger sponge construction: the center of the cube and the centers of its six faces.
%C A395241 Partial sums of A154105.
%C A395241 The odd-indexed terms of A011934 are A103532, so the alternating sums of cubes interleave this sequence and A103532, and the identity A011934(m-1) + A011934(m) = m^3 is the complement identity above.
%C A395241 For n = 2 and n = 3 these are the 44 and 135 cells removed at each iteration of the generalized Menger sponges with subdivision 5 and 7 described in the Bourke link.
%H A395241 Paul Bourke, <a href="https://paulbourke.net/fractals/mrlymath/">mrly fractals: Menger, Sierpinski, Cantor</a>
%H A395241 Carlo Mitchener, <a href="https://paulbourke.net/fractals/mrlymath/mrlymath.pdf">Marley Math: Cantor Sets, Sierpinski Carpets, Menger Sponges, And More</a>
%H A395241 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,-6,4,-1).
%F A395241 G.f.: x*(7 + 16*x + x^2)/(1 - x)^4.
%F A395241 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) - 6*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - a(n-4) for n > 3.
%F A395241 a(n) = A011934(2*n).
%F A395241 E.g.f.: exp(x)*x*(7 + 15*x + 4*x^2). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 10 2026
%o A395241 (Python)
%o A395241 def a(n): return n**2 * (4*n + 3)
%Y A395241 Cf. A011934, A103532, A154105, A016755.
%K A395241 nonn,easy,new
%O A395241 0,2
%A A395241 _Carlo Mitchener_, Jun 10 2026
